profiles, but unfortunately a linear ansatz for time-dependent
homogeneous solutions  leads to only trivial solutions
(see Ref. ). Even though we exceed the validity
of the action, let us proceed for the moment and examine the
homogeneous tachyon solution. Noting that the D- system
reduces to the non-BPS brane system when we restrict the complex
tachyon  to take only real value , it is easy
to see that the classical solution presented in
Ref. ,
 
is the tachyon solution on the D- which we are looking for.
The imaginary part  of the complex tachyon appears in the
Lagrangian only in squared form and so the equation of motion for
