satisfied by .  However the "tachyonic" fluctuation from
 leads to a new feature which we call
the tachyonic S-brane. An effective
tachyonic S-brane action is discussed in Appendix .

Next, we consider the arrow (4) in this subsection, which
will provide another way to derive the S-brane action.
