Now consider those configurations which can be approximated by a
homogeneous region for , and a different homogeneous
region when .  For our purposes the two regions will
correspond to the S-brane region , and the tachyon
condensation region . When the D2-brane decays,
some energy will be dissipated or radiated away but the electric flux
 
will be preserved.
The final state of the process should be
the most energy-efficient configuration for a given flux.

According to (),
the energy in the region of tachyon condensation
can be arbitrarily close to zero.
