Let us move on to the evaluation of the energy of the boosted
S-brane which is a timelike object. It is straightforward to show
that the rolling tachyon solution in the presence of a constant
magnetic field is also a solution of the non-BPS D2-brane system
(),
 
Basically we can turn on the constant field strength transverse
to the S-brane freely. Next, consider the boosted solution
 
where
 
Here the open string metric is
 
One can show that () is again a
solution(The nontrivial check is
on the equations of motion for the gauge fields. The tachyon
equation of motion is trivially satisfied since we made a boost
respecting the open string metric.)  of the non-BPS D2-brane
system ().  In the limit
 
the S-brane becomes timelike and in this case the tachyon
configuration is approximately
 
which resembles
the usual D-string kink solution.
This suggests that the energy is localized at .

We keep this in mind and proceed to carefully evaluate the
Hamiltonian at  for simplicity. The asymptotic expansion
of  at  is
 
